dcterms:description: A dataset acquired from 49 participants, capturing hand-drawn data to distinguish Parkinson's disease patients from healthy control subjects. It includes six time sequence parameters: azimuth, altitude, pressure, timestamp, x-Axis, and y-Axis.
dcterms:title: DraWritePD

dcterms:description: A dataset of signals extracted from an electronic smart pen, used to distinguish Parkinson's disease from healthy control subjects through image recognition tasks.
dcterms:title: NewHandPD

dcterms:description: A dataset consisting of subtle tremor signals captured from digital Luria alternating series tests, used to reflect the degree of tremor during fine movements.
dcterms:title: dLAST
